BinarySearch
Aim:
To write a C program to search an element using the Binary Search technique.

Algorithm:
Start.
Read the number of elements n.
Read n elements in ascending order into an array.
Read the element key to be searched.
Initialize start = 0, end = n - 1.
Repeat while start <= end:
Find mid = (start + end) / 2.
If arr[mid] == key, print “Element found” and stop.
If arr[mid] < key, set start = mid + 1.
Else set end = mid - 1.
If not found, display “Element not found”.
Stop.

Program:
#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
    int n, key, start, end, mid;
    printf("Enter the value of n: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    int arr[n];
    printf("Enter %d values for array:\n", n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        scanf("%d", &arr[i]);
    }
    printf("Enter element to be searched: ");
    scanf("%d", &key);

    start = 0;
    end = n - 1;

    while (start <= end)
    {
        mid = (start + end) / 2;

        if (arr[mid] == key)
        {
            printf("Element %d found at the index: %d", key, mid);
            return 0;
        }
        else if (arr[mid] < key)
        {
            start = mid + 1;
        }
        else
        {
            end = mid - 1;
        }
    }
    printf("Element not found: %d", key);
    return 0;
}

Output:
Enter the value of n:5
enter 5 value for array:
1
2
3
4
6
Enter element to be searched:8
element not found in 8

 Result: Program executed successfully and displayed correct search results.
